# Secrets (NEVER commit)
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
pull-secret*
secret*
SECRET*

# Byte-preserved sealed verification bundles are tracked in full. Their agent
# names (secret-reader, secret-report-writer) and reports (secrets-latest.md)
# collide with the secret*/SECRET* patterns above (case-insensitive on Windows);
# without this negation the redaction-proof artifacts would be silently dropped
# and the bundle SEAL would fail on a fresh clone.
!docs/internal/verification/**

# Same collision, different real source/template files matched by the bare
# secret*/SECRET* globs above: TAAR's secret_check builtin (a redaction-only
# scanner, not a secret itself - see its own module docstring) and the Helm
# Secret template (a stringData reference to .Values.secrets.api.token, no
# literal value). Both were silently untracked on every clone/CI checkout
# until this negation (discovered 2026-07-13 chasing a CI test-collection
# failure on a fresh Linux checkout).
!packages/taar/src/taar/checks/secret_check.py
!helm/project-ai/templates/secrets.yaml

# Exception to the negation above: the 2026-07-10 audit receipt bundle's 36 MB
# HEAD tarball stays out of git (reproducible via `git archive HEAD`; its
# SHA-256 is recorded in the bundle's SHA256SUMS.txt). Must follow the
# !docs/internal/verification/** line — last match wins.
docs/internal/verification/project-ai-receipts-2026-07-10/archive/

